## SC-300 ‚Äî Lab 4: Authentication Methods & MFA

## Phase: Phase 1 ‚Äì Core Identity Foundation
Goal

To configure authentication methods in Microsoft Entra ID, enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA), and understand how strong authentication protects identities.



## Why this lab matters

Most real breaches happen because of:
	‚Ä¢	Password-only authentication
	‚Ä¢	Weak credentials
	‚Ä¢	Stolen usernames

MFA is the single most effective identity security control.


## Lab Environment
	‚Ä¢	Microsoft Entra ID (cloud-only tenant)
	‚Ä¢	Microsoft Entra Admin Center
	‚Ä¢	Role used: Global Administrator (lab tenant only)
	‚Ä¢	Portal: https://entra.microsoft.com



## Steps


## Step 1 ‚Äî Review Authentication Methods

Navigate to:

Entra ID ‚Üí Protection ‚Üí Authentication methods

Review available methods:
	‚Ä¢	Microsoft Authenticator
	‚Ä¢	SMS
	‚Ä¢	Voice call
	‚Ä¢	Temporary Access Pass (TAP)
	‚Ä¢	FIDO2 security keys
	‚Ä¢	Email OTP (for guests)

‚ö†Ô∏è Do NOT disable anything yet.

Purpose:
Understand which methods Entra supports and how authentication is controlled centrally.



## Step 2 ‚Äî Enable Microsoft Authenticator
	1.	Click Microsoft Authenticator
	2.	Set Enable = Yes
	3.	Target:
	‚Ä¢	All users (lab tenant)
	4.	Save

Purpose:
Allows users to register and use the Authenticator app for MFA.


## Step 3 ‚Äî Enable Temporary Access Pass (TAP)
	1.	Click Temporary Access Pass
	2.	Enable policy
	3.	Configure:
	‚Ä¢	Lifetime: 1 hour (recommended for lab)
	‚Ä¢	One-time use: Yes
	4.	Target: All users
	5.	Save

Purpose:
Used for onboarding users without passwords.

üî• Very important exam concept.


## Step 4 ‚Äî Review Authentication Method Policies

Navigate back and observe:
	‚Ä¢	Each method can be enabled/disabled
	‚Ä¢	Policies are centrally controlled
	‚Ä¢	Methods can be targeted by group

Understand this concept:

Authentication methods define how users authenticate, not when.

(Conditional Access controls when ‚Äî later labs.)


## Step 5 ‚Äî Review User Authentication Methods
	1.	Go to Entra ID ‚Üí Users
	2.	Select lab-user1
	3.	Click Authentication methods

Observe:
	‚Ä¢	No MFA registered yet
	‚Ä¢	Methods are allowed but not enforced

This distinction matters.


## What You Learned
	‚Ä¢	Authentication methods are managed centrally in Entra ID
	‚Ä¢	MFA provides additional verification beyond passwords
	‚Ä¢	Microsoft Authenticator is the primary MFA method
	‚Ä¢	Temporary Access Pass supports secure onboarding
	‚Ä¢	Authentication methods ‚â† Conditional Access
	‚Ä¢	Users can authenticate only using enabled methods

	## Screenshoots Include:
  1.	Authentication methods overview page
	2.	Microsoft Authenticator enabled
	3.	Temporary Access Pass enabled
	4.	User authentication methods page

